                                "V1": "Click Save As."
                            },
                            "STEP_4": {
                                "V1": "In the Save As Type drop-down menu, select DOCX."
                            },
                            "STEP_5": {
                                "V1": "Open the newly saved file to ensure that the content and formatting have been preserved correctly. Check for any inconsistencies or errors that may have occurred during the conversion process."
                            }
                        },
                        "HEADING_1": {
                            "V1": "Resolving Outdated Format Issues"
                        },
                        "HEADING_1_DESC": {
                            "V1": "To ensure compatibility, improved functionality, and security, it is important to convert your documents to the latest file formats."
                        },
                        "HEADING_2": {
                            "V1": "For Microsoft Office 365 Users"
                        },
                        "HEADING_3": {
                            "V1": "Additional Tips"
                        },
                        "HEADING_3_1": {
                            "V1": "If you have multiple files to convert, consider using batch-conversion tools available within Microsoft 365 or third-party software to save time."
                        },
                        "HEADING_3_2": {
                            "V1": "Ensure that your Microsoft 365 suite is up to date to avoid compatibility issues with newer file formats."
                        }
                    }
                }
            },
            "EXCEL": {
                "ISSUE": {
                    "HyperlinkContentIssue": {
                        "FIXING_ISSUE_MICROSOFT_USERS": {
                            "HEADING": {
                                "V1": "For Microsoft Office 365 Users"
                            },
                            "STEP_1": {
                                "V1": "Right click on the hyperlink."
                            }
                        },
                        "HEADING": {
                            "V1": "Resolve hyperlink accessibility issues"
                        },
                        "REFERENCE_TO_WCAG_GUIDELINE": {
                            "V1": "See more information on the WCAG Guideline"
                        },
                        "REFERENCE_TO_WCAG_GUIDELINE_LINK": {
                            "V1": "2.4.4 Link Purpose (In Context)"
                        },
                        "SUB_HEADING": {
                            "V1": "When you insert a hyperlink into a document, having a description for the link is necessary in order to improve the accessibility of the document. Often times, the url does not provide enough information on the content residing inside the link."
                        }
                    },
                    "LowContrastIssue": {
                        "FIXING_ISSUE_MICROSOFT_USERS": {
                            "HEADING": {
                                "V1": "For Microsoft Excel Users"
                            },
                            "STEP_1": {
                                "V1": "Highlight the text that has the low color contrast issue."
                            },
                            "STEP_2": {
                                "V1": "Within the mini toolbar above the highlighted text, change the font color of the text until you meet the minimum contrast ratio.",
                                "V2": "You can check the current text color and background color using a color contrast tool, such as <0>WebAIM Contrast Checker</0>."
                            }
                        },
                        "HEADING": {
                            "V1": "Resolving Insufficient Contrast Issues"
                        },
                        "SUB_HEADING": {
                            "V1": "When there is insufficient contrast between the foreground text and the background, it can be difficult to read the text. Textual content should have high contrast ratios against their backgrounds in order to be legible to your readers. "
                        },
                        "REFERENCE_TO_WCAG_GUIDELINE": {
                            "V1": "See more information on the WCAG Guideline"
                        },
                        "REFERENCE_TO_WCAG_GUIDELINE_LINK": {
                            "V1": "1.4.3 / 1.4.6 Contrast"
                        }
                    },
