                        },
                        "STEP_1": {
                            "V1": "In your HTML code, locate the <0>&lt;li&gt;</0> element that is not placed within a list container (e.g., <0>&lt;ul&gt;</0>, <0>&lt;ol&gt;</0>, or <0>&lt;menu&gt;</0>)."
                        },
                        "STEP_2": {
                            "V1": "Fix the issue by either:",
                            "1": "<0>Wrap the &lt;li&gt; element in a list</0>: If the content in your <0>&lt;li&gt;</0> belongs to a list, place the <0>&lt;li&gt;</0> element within a list container (e.g., <0>&lt;ul&gt;</0>, <0>&lt;ol&gt;</0>, or <0>&lt;menu&gt;</0>). ",
                            "2": "<0>Change the &lt;li&gt; element into another element</0>: If the content in your <0>&lt;li&gt;</0> is not part of a list, replace the <0>&lt;li&gt;</0> element with another element (e.g., <0>&lt;div&gt;</0>, <0>&lt;span&gt;</0>, or <0>&lt;h2&gt;</0>)."
